td.p:
The Moorburg coal-fired power plant is situated within the port of Hamburg, on the south bank of the southern section of the Elbe river which, as a migratory route for certain fish species listed in Annex II to the Habitats Directive, namely river lamprey (
Lampetra fluviatilis
), sea lamprey (
Petromyzon marinus
) and salmon (
Salmo salar
), plays an important role in a number of Natura 2000 areas situated upstream of the Geesthacht weir (Germany) whose conservation objectives cover those species. Those areas are situated in the Länder of Lower Saxony, Mecklenburg-Vorpommern, Saxony-Anhalt, Brandenburg and Saxony, up to a distance of approximately 600 km from the plant. The Geesthacht weir is situated on the Elbe corridor, in between the Moorburg power plant and the Natura 2000 areas.
